   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter" part="N" org="uniform" sample="complete">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Bodleian_702_1841-04-04_page01.jpg"/>
            <dateline>
               <date when="1841-04-04" instant="false">
                  <note anchored="true">Ap 4. 1841</note>
               </date>
            </dateline>
            <p part="N">
               
               (7
               Apprehension had I of her danger insomuch<lb/>
               had <persName ref="./Personography.xml#AshbX1" instant="false" full="yes">Ashburner</persName> assured me she was going on well<lb/>
               (I remember his expression she may build Chateaux<lb/>
               on <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#SP" instant="false" full="yes">Espagne</placeName> now -if she pleases)<lb/>
               that I accepted yesterday morning actually<lb/>
               yesterday morning an invitation which had <lb/>
               been a dozen times repeated <del instant="false" status="unremarkable">&amp; wished for</del> by<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#RogeX1" instant="false" full="yes">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>Rogers</persName> to go to one of his breakfasts <del instant="false" status="unremarkable">&amp; it was</del>
               <lb/>
               a breakfast made on purpose for me with carte<lb/>
               blanche for my kith &amp; kin whom <persName ref="./Personography.xml#RogeX1" instant="false" full="yes">Rogers</persName> discovered<lb/>
               good natured man to be essential to my pleasure<lb/>
            </p>
            <p part="N">
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BeauF1" instant="false" full="yes">Capt<hi rend="superscript">n</hi> Beaufort</persName> , thinks of that too! wished to<lb/>
               go and asked me to introduce him &amp; <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BeauH1" instant="false" full="yes">Honora</persName> and<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeR2" instant="false" full="yes">Rosa</persName>and <persName ref="./Personography.xml#HollX1"
                         cert="low"
                         instant="false"
                         full="yes">Emily</persName> all dined much to <unclear instant="false"/> so they<lb/>
               had invites special and <persName ref="./Personography.xml#WilsL1" instant="false" full="yes">Lestock</persName> but he c<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> not<lb/>
            </p>
            <p part="N">
               So we all went and saw his fine pictures<lb/>
               &amp; all his delightful things himself by far the<lb/>
               most delightful among them notwithstanding<lb/>
               all that nature did to forbid - If not the best<lb/>
               worth seeing <persName ref="./Personography.xml#RogeX1" instant="false" full="yes">Rogers</persName> is certainly one of the men best<lb/>
               worth hearing of modern conversation men<lb/>
            </p>
            <p part="N">
               Too <unclear instant="false">tender</unclear> there was an admirable <choice>
                  <orig>breaf<lb/> 
                     fast</orig>
                  <reg instant="false">breakfast</reg>
               </choice>
               and we had it and him &amp; all of it to ourselves<lb/>
               the only thing I thought de trop was<lb/>
               one of the footmen - there were two in<lb/>
               waiting all Breakfast now one I<lb/>
               thought was <unclear instant="false"/> de trop -<lb/>
               in former times 20 years or 10 years<lb/>
               ago one footman or man of some kind<lb/>
               at a private breakfast was enough for a <hi rend="underline">marquess</hi>or <hi rend="underline">quis</hi>quis<lb/>
            </p>
            <p part="N">
               But let this pass nobody complained of it - and I<lb/>
               enjoyed the full and complete satisfaction of seeing <lb/>
               all my kith and kin pleased - delighted - even<lb/>
               the fastidious captain his self -<lb/>
            </p>
            <p part="N">
               But only think how near pleasure &amp; pain - <choice>
                  <orig>feast<lb/> 
                     ing</orig>
                  <reg instant="false">feasting</reg>
               </choice>
               &amp; revelry and all that happened that night<lb/>
               At parting with <persName ref="./Personography.xml#RogeX1" instant="false" full="yes">Rogers</persName> he holding both my hands<lb/>
               so pressed me to come back again &amp; breakfast once more all<lb/>
               <unclear instant="false"/> - yes these young ones whom I find <unclear instant="false">are of</unclear>
               <unclear instant="false"/>
               <lb/>
               <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Bodleian_702_1841-04-04_page02.jpg"/>
               8) 
               have adopted" that I could not refuse the dear dead<lb/>
               dandy the sincerely good natured benevolent<lb/>
               flattering sensitive sensible charming ugly oldest<lb/>
               of men extant - so I accepted for Monday or Wednesday<lb/>
               &amp; agreed to write and say which -<lb/>
            </p>
            <p part="N">
               And this day I have been writing to him to<lb/>
               say how it is with us now! - And to break this<lb/>
               and all other engagements specially one with<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#CornX1" instant="false" full="yes">Lady Cornwallis</persName> the object &amp; cause of which I have<lb/>
               not time here to explain nor can you care about<lb/>
               it - at present.<lb/>
            </p>
            <p part="N">
               I will now make up my packet that I<lb/>
               may go into the post this sunday night for that<lb/>
               much it <unclear instant="false">can</unclear>do and that will secure its going<lb/>
               by first mail that steams -<lb/>
            </p>
            <p part="N">
                  Never did I see a more tender kind husband<lb/>
                  than <persName ref="./Personography.xml#WilsL1" instant="false" full="yes">Lestock</persName>- <persName ref="./Personography.xml#TennM1"
                         cert="medium"
                         instant="false"
                         full="yes">
                  <choice>
                     <orig>Mariquetta</orig>
                     <reg instant="false">Mariquita</reg>
                  </choice>
               </persName> may think or say<lb/>
                 
                  what she pleases about <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeF1"
                         cert="high"
                         instant="false"
                         full="yes">Francis</persName> ! - he has never<lb/>
                  been so tried &amp; I hope never will<lb/>
            </p>
            <closer>
               Farewell dearest <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeF2" instant="false" full="yes">mother</persName> &amp; do let your<lb/>
               self be taken care of &amp; your legs tied till you<lb/>
               are fit to go - or come<lb/> 
               Yours affectionately<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1" instant="false" full="yes">Maria Edgeworth</persName>
               <lb/>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
               <p part="N"> 1/2 after 5 Eve<hi rend="superscript">g</hi>
                  <lb/>
                  I have opened my letter to insert something <choice>
                     <orig>Asburn<lb/> 
                        -er</orig>
                     <reg instant="false">
                        <persName ref="./Personography.xml#AshbX1" instant="false" full="yes">Ashburner</persName>
                     </reg>
                  </choice>
                  said (of which I have not a very clear idea<lb/>
                  but the words may never nevertheless convey some<lb/>
                  dear and important idea to you<lb/>
                  <del instant="false" status="unremarkable">
                     <unclear instant="false">"We must</unclear> keep up this <hi rend="underline">discharge</hi> this discharge</del>
                  <lb/>
                  <del instant="false" status="unremarkable">must be kept up "-</del>
                  <lb/>
                  <del instant="false" status="unremarkable">and I am not sure but that the fomentation was</del>
                  <lb/>
                  <del instant="false" status="unremarkable">for that purpose instead of for aiding <unclear instant="false">medicine</unclear>
                     <choice>
                        <orig>operat<lb/> 
                        ing</orig>
                        <reg instant="false">operating</reg>
                     </choice>
                  </del>
                  <lb/>
                  <del instant="false" status="unremarkable">ing on the bowels - all the satisfaction is that I have</del>
                  <lb/>
                  <del instant="false" status="unremarkable">told you all this now - &amp; <unclear instant="false">
                        <choice>
                           <orig>alott</orig>
                           <reg instant="false">a lot</reg>
                        </choice> more</unclear>
                  </del>
                  <lb/>
                  <del instant="false" status="unremarkable">for you to make the best of it</del>
                  <lb/>
               </p>
            </postscript>
         </div>
